duck: Molar (grape), another name for the Spanish wine grape Listan Negro
Molar (tooth), the fourth kind of tooth in mammals
Molar volume - The molar volume, symbol Vm, is the volume occupied by one mole of a substance at a given temperature and pressure.
molar definition: a tooth with a rounded or flattened surface adapted for grinding; '''specifically''' one of the cheek teeth in mammals behind the incisors and canines.
El Molar, Tarragona, a village in the comarca (county) of Priorat, province of Tarragona in the autonomous region of Catalonia, Spain
El Molar, Madrid, a town in the north of the Community of Madrid in the road to Burgos, after San Agustín de Guadalix
Molar behavior, or molara, larger units of behavior in psychology
Molar concentration, a unit of concentration, or molarity, of solutions equal to 1 mole per litre

wiki.text:
'Molar' may refer to:

*Molar (tooth), the fourth kind of tooth in mammals *Molar (grape), another name
for the Spanish wine grape Listan Negro *Molar concentration, a unit of
concentration, or molarity, of solutions equal to 1 mole per litre *Molar volume
*El Molar, Tarragona, a village in the comarca (county) of Priorat, province of
Tarragona in the autonomous region of Catalonia, Spain *El Molar, Madrid, a town
in the north of the Community of Madrid in the road to Burgos, after San Agustín
de Guadalix *Molar behavior, or molara, larger units of behavior in psychology

See also:
* Moler, a power-pop band from Australia
